al to professional medicine and now less common. The authors report on both the physical effects of herbal remedies and the psychological factors that have an impact on their success. Trying to Give Ease is a companion to A Reference Guide to Medicinal Plants, also published by Duke University Press.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aHerbsxTherapeutic usezAppalachian Region. 0aMateria medica, VegetablezAppalachian Region. 0aMedicinal plantszAppalachian Region. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Herbal Medications.2bisacsh1 aPhilpott, Jane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822379683zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822379683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822379683.jpg  a978-3-11-071360-2  DUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles